---
const guidanceUrl = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_CALENDAR_URL?.trim() || "https://cal.com/chaiwithjai/ai-guidance-counselor";
const trainingUrl = "https://cal.com/chaiwithjai/codex-claude-code-training";
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Dharmic Data | Making AI useful in real life</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Jai Bhagat helps people choose, build, and judge one useful AI workflow at a time while documenting the path toward a public-interest collective." />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Dharmic Data | Making AI useful in real life" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Paid guidance now. Public demos and a documented path toward a collective by June 2027." />
    <meta property="og:image" content="/assets/cdn/69577d21-69579e3f1cc3870da71214e1_Social-share-1-.webp" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/dharmic-assets/shakti-seva-mark.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/mission.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to the story</a>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="Dharmic Data home">
        <img src="/dharmic-assets/dharmic-data-logo.svg" alt="Dharmic Data" />
      </a>
      <button class="menu-button" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="site-nav">Menu</button>
      <nav id="site-nav" aria-label="Main navigation">
        <a href="#story">Why this exists</a>
        <a href="#method">How I work</a>
        <a href="#roadmap">Road to 2027</a>
        <a href="/vlog">Build stories</a>
      </nav>
      <a class="nav-cta" href={guidanceUrl}>Book a session</a>
    </header>

    <main id="main">
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">A public-interest AI practice by Jai Bhagat</p>
          <h1>AI should leave people with more agency.</h1>
          <p class="hero-lead">I help people choose one useful AI project, test it against their real work, and learn enough to make the next decision for themselves.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button button-dark" href={guidanceUrl}>Book AI guidance · $125</a>
            <a class="text-link" href="#story">Read why I am building this</a>
          </div>
          <p class="offer-preview">In 60 minutes, we will define a use case, choose a tool, set data boundaries, and write a 30 day test plan.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stage" aria-label="Animated Dharmic Data character">
          <div class="stage-note note-one">Start with the work</div>
          <div class="stage-note note-two">Test before expanding</div>
          <div class="home-rive" data-rive-url="/assets/cdn/69577d21-6995b79cfaa7bf474085d59c_home_page_character_1-1-.riv" data-rive-state-machine="State Machine 1" data-rive-artboard="Artboard" data-rive-autoplay="true" data-rive-fit="cover" data-rive-alignment="center" data-animation-type="rive"><canvas></canvas></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="proof-strip" aria-label="Experience and teaching proof">
        <div><strong>10+ years</strong><span>in software and teaching</span></div>
        <div><strong>4.9 / 5.0</strong><span>instructor rating</span></div>
        <div><strong>HashiCorp</strong><span>production engineering</span></div>
        <div><strong>Parsons</strong><span>adult instruction</span></div>
      </section>

      <section id="story" class="story section-pad">
        <div class="story-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">The honest version</p>
          <h2>This is the in-between period.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="story-body">
          <p class="story-lead">For years, I taught economic empowerment work for free. I am now turning that practice into a public effort that can last beyond my calendar.</p>
          <p>Dharmic Data is not a nonprofit today. Between now and June 2027, I am using paid sessions to fund the time, publish working demos, document what succeeds and fails, and learn what a future collective should become.</p>
          <p>I have spent more than ten years moving between software and teaching. I shipped production software at HashiCorp, taught JavaScript at Parsons, and helped Queens founders and operators use AI in work they already care about. That mix shapes every project here.</p>
          <a class="text-link light" href="https://chaiwithjai.com/about">Read Jai's full background</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="method" class="method section-pad">
        <header class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">What makes this different</p>
          <h2>Start with your work. Keep the judgment visible.</h2>
          <p>I am interested in AI when it gives a person more control over useful work. I pass when a simpler system is safer or clearer.</p>
        </header>
        <ol class="method-grid">
          <li><span>01</span><h3>Name the recurring problem</h3><p>We begin with work that already costs you time or attention. We do not begin with a model.</p></li>
          <li><span>02</span><h3>Use real constraints</h3><p>We test against your files, repository, public data, time, and machine when it is safe to do so.</p></li>
          <li><span>03</span><h3>Set the boundary</h3><p>We decide what the model may read and which choices or actions always need human review.</p></li>
          <li><span>04</span><h3>Make one small test</h3><p>We measure one useful task before we automate a whole job or buy more infrastructure.</p></li>
          <li><span>05</span><h3>Show the evidence</h3><p>Public projects include sources, traces, evaluations, limits, and postmortems.</p></li>
          <li><span>06</span><h3>Know when to pass</h3><p>If ordinary code or a person makes the better decision, AI stays out of that step.</p></li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="case-study section-pad">
        <div class="case-visual">
          <img src="/dharmic-assets/shakti-live-result.png" alt="Shakti showing the public record for a New York City building" />
          <div class="case-stamp">Working public demo</div>
        </div>
        <div class="case-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Proof, not a promise</p>
          <h2>Shakti shows the method in public.</h2>
          <p>Shakti helps a New Yorker read public housing repair records for one building. The public lookup uses ordinary code, not AI. It shows its City sources, keeps unit details out of the result, and links every building through the City's identifier.</p>
          <p>The optional local edition gives Hermes a treated packet to explain. The model cannot change the address match, counts, or public next step.</p>
          <div class="case-actions">
            <a class="button button-dark" href="https://shakti.dharmicdata.org">Try the live lookup</a>
            <a class="text-link" href="https://github.com/ChaiWithJai/shakti-seva-studio">Inspect the repository</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="offer section-pad" aria-labelledby="offer-title">
        <div class="offer-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">The offer today</p>
          <h2 id="offer-title">Bring the AI decision you keep circling.</h2>
          <p>We will turn it into one useful next step. You do not need a polished idea or a technical background.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>A defined first use case</li>
            <li>A local, subscription, or API recommendation</li>
            <li>Clear data and action boundaries</li>
            <li>A written 30 day test plan</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <aside class="offer-card">
          <p class="eyebrow">AI Guidance Counselor</p>
          <div class="price"><strong>$125</strong><span>60 minutes</span></div>
          <p>Guidance and project definition with Jai. This is not a promise of a finished software build.</p>
          <a class="button button-coral" href={guidanceUrl}>Choose a time</a>
          <p class="small">If you already use Codex or Claude Code and want repository training, a 45 minute session is also available for $85.</p>
          <a class="text-link" href={trainingUrl}>See code training</a>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <section class="voices section-pad" aria-labelledby="voices-title">
        <header class="section-heading compact">
          <p class="eyebrow">What people carried forward</p>
          <h2 id="voices-title">The work should make the next step feel possible.</h2>
        </header>
        <div class="quote-grid">
          <figure><blockquote>"This class really changed my mindset. I feel empowered."</blockquote><figcaption>Toya, QEDC workshop graduate</figcaption></figure>
          <figure><blockquote>"I can't thank Jai enough for opening my eyes to what's possible with AI."</blockquote><figcaption>Samina Quraishi, small business owner</figcaption></figure>
          <figure><blockquote>"I went from being scared of being replaced to feeling like I had a thinking partner."</blockquote><figcaption>Seema Kothari, real estate</figcaption></figure>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="roadmap" class="roadmap section-pad">
        <div class="roadmap-copy">
          <p class="eyebrow">Now through June 2027</p>
          <h2>Paid guidance seeds the public work.</h2>
          <p>The goal is a model where useful teaching and open projects support each other. I am documenting the path so other people can judge it, copy what works, or help shape it.</p>
        </div>
        <ol class="timeline">
          <li><span>Now</span><strong>Rent the calendar</strong><p>One-to-one guidance pays for the time to teach, build, and publish.</p></li>
          <li><span>Next</span><strong>Test small learning rooms</strong><p>Private cohorts, short courses, and a Dogged Pursuits practice room may run with clear, modest promises. They are not for sale yet.</p></li>
          <li><span>June 2027</span><strong>Seed the collective</strong><p>Use the evidence from this period to shape a nonprofit collective for public demos, practical teaching, and shared methods.</p></li>
        </ol>
        <div class="idea-rive" data-rive-url="/assets/cdn/69577d21-6995b79cd68776d3c9ca5a07_home-page-bowl-charater-2-1-.riv" data-rive-state-machine="State Machine 1" data-rive-artboard="Artboard" data-rive-autoplay="true" data-rive-fit="cover" data-rive-alignment="center" data-animation-type="rive"><canvas></canvas></div>
      </section>

      <section class="final-cta section-pad">
        <p class="eyebrow">A useful first move</p>
        <h2>Bring one real problem. Leave with a test you can run.</h2>
        <p>Every paid session helps fund the public experiments and teaching documented here.</p>
        <a class="button button-dark" href={guidanceUrl}>Book AI guidance · $125</a>
        <div class="footer-rive desk" data-rive-url="/assets/cdn/69577d21-6995b79cb5c877d98300cec7_footer-bowl-character-animation-3.riv" data-rive-state-machine="State Machine 1" data-rive-artboard="Artboard" data-rive-autoplay="true" data-rive-fit="contain" data-rive-alignment="center" data-animation-type="rive"><canvas></canvas></div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <img src="/dharmic-assets/dharmic-data-logo.svg" alt="Dharmic Data" />
      <p>Independent project. Working toward a nonprofit collective. Not a registered nonprofit today.</p>
      <nav aria-label="Footer navigation"><a href="/vlog">Build stories</a><a href="https://github.com/ChaiWithJai/dharmic-data">Source</a><a href="https://chaiwithjai.com/about">About Jai</a></nav>
    </footer>

    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/jquery-3.5.1.min.dc5e7f18c8.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/webflow.schunk.7a4a7f019cc01602.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/webflow.schunk.90febbc43c629f61.js"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/webflow.73431be6.2c71108c00d371a3.js"></script>
    <script is:inline>
      const button = document.querySelector('.menu-button');
      const nav = document.querySelector('#site-nav');
      button?.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const open = button.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
        button.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!open));
        nav?.toggleAttribute('data-open', !open);
      });
      nav?.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
        if (event.target instanceof HTMLAnchorElement) {
          button?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
          nav.removeAttribute('data-open');
        }
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
